record FpML5.reporting.CashflowCalculationElements {
  numberOfUnits : FpML5.reporting.UnderlyerReferenceUnits?

  # Identifies the notional in effect for this calculation period.
  notional : FpML5.reporting.CashflowNotional?

  # The underlyer(s) used to calculate the amount of this cashflow component. The underlyer(s) will remain unaltered from the values specified in the underlying transaction (i.e. the Fixed Rate on a Credit Default Swap).
  underlyer : FpML5.reporting.TradeUnderlyer?

  # The computed rate(s) or price(s) used to calculate the amount of this cashflow component. These computed rates or prices may include averaging and/or various types of rate treatment rules.
  calculatedRate : FpML5.reporting.CashflowFixing?

  # The period details for calculation/accrual periods that comprise this cashflow component.
  calculationPeriod : FpML5.reporting.CashflowCalculationPeriod?

}

notional.Doc: Identifies the notional in effect for this calculation period.
notional.Name: notional

underlyer.Doc: The underlyer(s) used to calculate the amount of this cashflow component. The underlyer(s) will remain unaltered from the values specified in the underlying transaction (i.e. the Fixed Rate on a Credit Default Swap).
underlyer.Name: underlyer

calculatedRate.Doc: The computed rate(s) or price(s) used to calculate the amount of this cashflow component. These computed rates or prices may include averaging and/or various types of rate treatment rules.
calculatedRate.Name: calculatedRate

calculationPeriod.Doc: The period details for calculation/accrual periods that comprise this cashflow component.
calculationPeriod.Name: calculationPeriod
